    "constraints_html": "<span class=\"ref\" data-scene=\"transcript-absorb\">ProofShapeAir observes the VK pre-hash (DIGEST_SIZE elements) on its first row via TranscriptBus with is_sample=0</span>. When continuations are enabled, the pre-hash is also <span class=\"ref\" data-scene=\"prehash-publish\">sent on PreHashBus so the enclosing circuit can expose it as a public value</span>.",
    "soundness_html": "The pre-hash is a prover-supplied value absorbed into the Fiat-Shamir sponge, so it pins all downstream challenges via the Poseidon2 sponge chain. The subcircuit cannot constrain the pre-hash to equal hash(vk_child) directly (that would bake hash(vk_child) into the circuit's own VK, breaking self-verification); instead, the <span class=\"ref\" data-scene=\"prehash-publish\">enclosing circuit must verify pre-hash == hash(vk_child)</span>. This is the first assumption of the main claim."
  },
