    "constraints_html": "ProofShapeAir <span class=\"ref\" data-scene=\"transcript-observe\">observes common_main_commit (DIGEST_SIZE elements) on TranscriptBus</span>, and simultaneously <span class=\"ref\" data-scene=\"commitments-provide\">sends it on CommitmentsBus with (major_idx=0, minor_idx=commit_index)</span> so MerkleVerifyAir can authenticate Merkle roots against it during WHIR query verification.",
    "soundness_html": "Because the <span class=\"ref\" data-scene=\"same-cell\">same cell is used for both the TranscriptBus observation and the CommitmentsBus send</span>, the extracted common_main_commit equals both the transcript-observed value and the Merkle root used for query verification. Any discrepancy would cause a bus imbalance on either TranscriptBus or CommitmentsBus."
